# tooling-hephaestus-implementer-no-changes-state-skip — History

## v1.2.0 (2026-06-08)

**Changed by:** PR #1100 — run_learn model parameter fix (ProjectHephaestus)
**Verification:** verified-precommit

### What changed
- Added "learn model parameter" section to Verified Workflow: `run_learn()` in `learn.py` must accept `model: str | None = None` so callers can override the default `learn_model()` (Haiku); `_run_learn()` in `ImplementationPhaseRunner` passes `implementer_model()` so the `/learn` step uses the same model as the implementation
- Added new "When to Use" trigger: `run_learn()` invokes `learn_model()` (Haiku) but the caller (`_run_learn` on `ImplementationPhaseRunner`) should pass `implementer_model()`
- Added 1 new Failed Attempts row
- Added new Verified On entry (PR #1100)
- Bumped version 1.1.0 → 1.2.0

### Why
`run_learn()` was hardcoded to use `learn_model()` (Haiku) regardless of which model the
implementer session ran with. When resumed from `_run_learn()` in `ImplementationPhaseRunner`,
the `/learn` step needs to use `implementer_model()` to avoid the capability mismatch of
having a Haiku session pick up an Opus/Sonnet implementation transcript.

